of the street.  A few trees line the western side.

description: Beyond the residential homes and buildings of New Vector's most
northern street stands the large brick city wall that protects the
entire city.  The neighborhood this street runs through is well kept
with modest homes on either side, made from the same brick seen all
around the city.  Eastwards the boulevard continues with the northern
wall and intersects with B and A Street, ending at Z Street.
Westwards it comes to an end at the northwest corner of New Vector
City with D Street.
{x
94303.name: {c-[ {MN{morthway {MB{moulevard {c]-{x

description: A large stone square appears, named after the current Emperor of
Vector and the first newly   {M--    --{x  constructed item at the Fortress
since its own deconstruction {M||   //{x  and the end of War between itself
and the Tripower Kingdom.    {M||  //{x  Beyond this square lies what is
known as New Vector City,    {M|| //{x  built from the remains of the old
fortress and recycled iron   {M||//{x  from soldiers armor and old magitek
machinery.  Southwards lies  {M||\\{x  Castle Drive which leads to the old
Vectorian Castle, home of    {M|| \\{x  the Emperor.  Which was once a field
is now an industrial zone,   {M||  \\{x  and Workers Dormitories, the life
blood of the new city.       {M||   \\{x  North leads down A Street, one of
many new cookie cutter       {M--    --{x  streets built in this new city.
Eastwards the brick street of Main Street passes between two large brick
walls and beyond that, Old Vector City.  Westwards the street continues
to the center of New Vector City.
94200.name: {m-{M={c[{M K e f k a {*+{M S q u a r e {c]{M={m-{x

description: This street is one of the most eastern streets of the new city,
with the exception of Z Street which only runs a short distance north
of the Magitek Factory, located just east beyond the large brick wall
on the southern half of A Street.  Running mostly in the northern end
the occupied sides of the street are filled with upper class shops and
homes.
{x
94201.name: {c-[ {MA {MS{mtreet {c]-{x

description: Like most of the streets, avenues and boulevards of New Vector
City, this street resembles everything else.  The haste of the city
construction caused everything to seem the same, not helping was the
generic street names.  C Street here might look like A Street.  Only
the slight differences in the buildings and homes allow people to
navigate the city without getting lost.
{x
94250.name: {c-[ {MC {MS{mtreet {c]-{x

description: A large intersection opens up between D Street and A Avenue.
Connecting with D Street here is A Avenue which begins at its most
western location.  It stretches eastwards towards the Magitek Factory
and Geomancer Airship Fortress.  D Street runs north and south along
the western end of the city and its city wall, and is mostly made up
of people's homes.
94279.name: {MI{mntersection of {c[{MD S{mtreet{c] {m& {c[{MA A{mvenue{c]{x

description: If it wasn't for the different colors and styles of buildings, a
person could easily get very lost in New Vector City.  The city was
built quickly and utilizes the same design on all streets, making them
look like they were built from a cookie cutter.  Various buildings
though on either side allow people to not get totally lost.
Northwards D Street intersects with A Avenue and Northern Boulevard,
while southwards is Magitek Square and beyond that, B Avenue.
{x
94276.name: {c-[ {MD {MS{mtreet {c]-{x

description: Large trees line this boulevard, children can be seen playing on
the streets which are lined with modest homes.  Northern Boulevard
runs along side the giant brick city wall which can be seen beyond the
homes north of this street, protecting the city.  At night the street
is illuminated by the warm glow of Magicite Lamps.  Eastwards the
boulevard intersects and C, B and A Street coming to an end at the
northeast corner of New Vector City with Z Street.  Westwards only a
short distance is the northwest corner and the northern end of D
Street.
{x
94330.name: {c-[ {MN{morthway {MB{moulevard {c]-{x

description: Everything tends to look the same in this city, this avenue running
east to west looks just like the streets running north and south.  But
that's due to the haste this city was built with.  This land was once
a large field west of the Fortress of Vector, Soldiers of the old
Vectorian Army would have trained now where residents sleep.  New
bricks and recycled material from the fortress went in creating this
area.
{x
94282.name: {c-[ {MA A{mvenue {c]-{x

description: Large trees line this boulevard, children can be seen playing on
the streets which are lined with modest homes.  Northern Boulevard
runs along side the giant brick city wall which can be seen beyond the
homes north of this street, protecting the city.  At night the street
is illuminated by the warm glow of Magicite Lamps.  Westwards the
boulevards comes to the intersection with A Street.  Eastwards it
heads towards the northeast corner of New Vector City and the
intersection with Z Street.
{x
94319.name: {c-[ {MN{morthway {MB{moulevard {c]-{x

description: The stone street comes to an end here and turns eastwards or B
Avenue.  This is D Streets most southern end and is the most southwest
location of New Vector City.  Northwards the street follows along the
western side of the city and passes by Magitek Square and intersects
with A Avenue and Northern Boulevard.  B Avenue runs eastwards towards
the new industrial sector and intersects with C Street and B Street.
94270.name: {MI{mntersection of {c[{MD S{mtreet{c] {m& {c[{MB A{mvenue{c]{x

description: This avenue runs west to east along the southern end of New Vector
City and unlike its older brother A Avenue on the north end, the more
poorer citizens of the city live in these neighborhoods.  Far east at
the end of the south end is the Vectorian Industrial Sector, its large
smoke stacks standing tall and casting a shadow over these homes at
night.
{x
94252.name: {c-[ {MB A{mvenue {c]-{x

description: The brick street of Main Street continues its east-west path
through the depth of New Vector City.  Westwards you can make out the
giant stone wall of the new city and the end of street.  On either
side of the street are assorted buildings, homes and shops.  Eastward
the street heads towards Warhammer Square, City Center and Kefka
Square.  Beyond that is Old Vector City.  Westwards is Magitek Square,
the final square of the new city.
{x
94261.name: {c-[ {MM{main {MS{mtreet {MV{mector {c]-{x

description: Looking like every other intersection, A Street ends here with the
cities most northern street, smartly named Northern Boulevard.
Southwards the street intersects with A Avenue and ends at Kefka
Square.  Beyond the square southwards is the Vector City Industrial
Sector on Castle Drive.  From Kefka Square eastwards is Old Vector
City.  Northern Boulevard which follows the northern wall continues
here east to west.
